description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse seeking an exciting opportunity to work within North East Derbyshire or Chesterfield Integrated Community Nursing?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, this opportunity is for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There has never been a more exciting time to join one of the largest and constantly expanding specialist community NHS providers in the country – one that is also among the very best NHS employers, as voted by its own staff and rated as outstanding by CQC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated Community Services include experienced Nurses, Community Matrons, Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists, Clinical Support Workers and Adult Care staff who work collaboratively with GP Practice staff, Acute and Community Hospitals and Derbyshire County Adult Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Service is to provide holistic Nursing care in patients&#39; own homes and Residential Care Home settings, to prevent hospital admissions or facilitate early discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have various band 5 posts available within North East Derbyshire and Chesterfield providing care and support to patients in their own homes and care home settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is working within established teams and various hours are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Phil Parkes, Integrated Community team leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;philip.parkes@nhs.net, 07721 879764&lt;/p&gt;
